

Genesis
English: ESV
Actual Greek: LXX Rahlf's
Literal Greek: Translation
Actual Hebrew: HMT-W4
Literal Hebrew: Translation
Notes: Commentary Brienna DiPietro

Genesis.1.1
English: In the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth.
Actual Greek:	Ἐν ἀρχῇ ἐποίησεν ὁ θεὸς τὸν οὐρανὸν καὶ τὴν γῆν.
Literal Greek: In the beginning god made the heaven and the earth.
Actual Hebrew: בְּרֵאשִׁ֖ית בָּרָ֣א אֱלֹהִ֑ים אֵ֥ת הַשָּׁמַ֖יִם וְאֵ֥ת הָאָֽרֶץ׃
Literal Hebrew: at first God created the heavens and the earth
Notes:
nuances of first phrase, what's coming into being? putting together or creating

Genesis.1.2
English: The earth was without form and void, and darkness was over the face of the deep. And the Spirit of God was hovering over the face of the waters.
Actual Greek: ἡ δὲ γῆ ἦν ἀόρατος καὶ ἀκατασκεύαστος, καὶ σκότος ἐπάνω τῆς ἀβύσσου, καὶ πνεῦμα θεοῦ ἐπεφέρετο ἐπάνω τοῦ ὕδατος.
Literal Greek: and the earth was not visible and not formed, and darkness [was] above the abyss, and the breath of god was being brought above the water.
Actual Hebrew: וְהָאָ֗רֶץ הָיְתָ֥ה תֹ֨הוּ֙ וָבֹ֔הוּ וְחֹ֖שֶׁךְ עַל־פְּנֵ֣י תְה֑וֹם וְר֣וּחַ אֱלֹהִ֔ים מְרַחֶ֖פֶת עַל־פְּנֵ֥י הַמָּֽיִם
Literal Hebrew: and the earth was formless and empty and darkness [was] over the face of the abyss and the breath of God brooding over the face of the waters
Notes:
- Very liberal with the use of plurals from Greek to ESV
- Greek is totally different
- Piel verb מְרַחֶ֖פֶת and weird definition

Genesis.1.3
English: And God said, “Let there be light,” and there was light.
Actual Greek: καὶ εἶπεν ὁ θεός Γενηθήτω φῶς. καὶ ἐγένετο φῶς.
Literal Greek: and god said Let there be light. and light came to be.
Actual Hebrew:  וַיֹּ֥אמֶר אֱלֹהִ֖ים יְהִ֣י א֑וֹר וַֽיְהִי־אֽוֹר׃
Literal Hebrew: and God said let there be light and there was light
Notes:
- patterning of divine names in the Greek
      elohim, θεος: God
      YHWH, κύριος: the Lord


Genesis.1.4
English: And God saw that the light was good. And God separated the light from the darkness.
Actual Greek: καὶ εἶδεν ὁ θεὸς τὸ φῶς ὅτι καλόν. καὶ διεχώρισεν ὁ θεὸς ἀνὰ μέσον τοῦ φωτὸς καὶ ἀνὰ μέσον τοῦ σκότους.
Literal Greek: and god saw the light, that [it was] good. and god separated between the light and between the darkness.
Actual Hebrew: וַיַּ֧רְא אֱלֹהִ֛ים אֶת־הָא֖וֹר כִּי־ט֑וֹב וַיַּבְדֵּ֣ל אֱלֹהִ֔ים בֵּ֥ין הָא֖וֹר וּבֵ֥ין הַחֹֽשֶׁךְ׃
Literal Hebrew: and God saw the light that [it was] good and God separated the light and the darkness
Notes:
- κὰλον can be nom or acc

Genesis.1.5
English: God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And there was evening and there was morning, the first day.
Actual Greek: καὶ ἐκάλεσεν ὁ θεὸς τὸ φῶς ἡμέραν καὶ τὸ σκότος ἐκάλεσεν νύκτα. καὶ ἐγένετο ἑσπέρα καὶ ἐγένετο πρωί, ἡμέρα μία.
Literal Greek: and god called the light day and the darkness [he] called night. and night was and it was morning, day one
Actual Hebrew: וַיִּקְרָ֨א אֱלֹהִ֤ים ׀ לָאוֹר֙ י֔וֹם וְלַחֹ֖שֶׁךְ קָ֣רָא לָ֑יְלָה וַֽיְהִי־עֶ֥רֶב
Literal Hebrew: and God called to the light day and to the dark [he] called night and it was evening and it was morning, day one.
Notes:
- ἑσπέρα is a noun πρωί is an adverb
- ἐγένετο has creation in it; serious beef

Genesis.1.6
English: And God said, Let there be an expanse in the midst of the waters, and let it separate the waters from the waters.”
Actual Greek: Καὶ εἶπεν ὁ θεός Γενηθήτω στερέωμα ἐν μέσῳ τοῦ ὕδατος καὶ ἔστω διαχωρίζον ἀνὰ μέσον ὕδατος καὶ ὕδατος. καὶ ἐγένετο οὕτως.
Literal Greek: and God said Let there be firmament in the middle of the water and let it be separating between water and water. and like this it came to be.
Actual Hebrew: וַיֹּ֣אמֶר אֱלֹהִ֔ים יְהִ֥י רָקִ֖יעַ בְּת֣וֹךְ הַמָּ֑יִם וִיהִ֣י מַבְדִּ֔יל בֵּ֥ין מַ֖יִם לָמָֽיִם׃
Literal Hebrew: and God said let there be an expanse in the midst of the waters and let it there be a separation between the waters and the waters.
Notes:
- did it not come to be?

Genesis.1.7
English: And God made the expanse and separated the waters that were under the expanse from the waters that were above the expanse. And it was so.
Actual Greek:  καὶ ἐποίησεν ὁ θεὸς τὸ στερέωμα, καὶ διεχώρισεν ὁ θεὸς ἀνὰ μέσον τοῦ ὕδατος, ὃ ἦν ὑποκάτω τοῦ στερεώματος, καὶ ἀνὰ μέσον τοῦ ὕδατος τοῦ ἐπάνω τοῦ στερεώματος.
Literal Greek: and God made the firmament, and God separated between the water, which was below the firmament, and between the water above the firmament.
Actual Hebrew: וַיַּ֣עַשׂ אֱלֹהִים֮ אֶת־הָרָקִיעַ֒ וַיַּבְדֵּ֗ל בֵּ֤ין הַמַּ֙יִם֙ אֲשֶׁר֙ מִתַּ֣חַת לָרָקִ֔יעַ וּבֵ֣ין הַמַּ֔יִם אֲשֶׁ֖ר מֵעַ֣ל לָרָקִ֑יעַ וַֽיְהִי־כֵֽן׃
Literal Hebrew: and God made the expanse and [He] separated between the waters which [were] from below the expanse and between the waters which [were] above the expanse and so it came to be.
Notes:
- firmament/separator in Greek
- the Greek lacks so much parallelism
-

Genesis.1.8
English: And God called the expanse Heaven. And there was evening and there was morning, the second day.
Actual Greek: καὶ ἐκάλεσεν ὁ θεὸς τὸ στερέωμα οὐρανόν. καὶ εἶδεν ὁ θεὸς ὅτι καλόν. καὶ ἐγένετο ἑσπέρα καὶ ἐγένετο πρωί, ἡμέρα δευτέρα.
Literal Greek: and God called the firmament sky. and God saw that [it was] good. and night was and it was morning, day two.
Actual Hebrew:  וַיִּקְרָ֧א אֱלֹהִ֛ים לָֽרָקִ֖יעַ שָׁמָ֑יִם וַֽיְהִי־עֶ֥רֶב וַֽיְהִי־בֹ֖קֶר י֥וֹם שֵׁנִֽי׃
Literal Hebrew: and God called the expanse sky and it was evening and it was morning, the second day.
Notes
- did the Greeks even have the same general idea

Genesis.1.9
English: And God said, “Let the waters under the heavens be gathered together into one place, and let the dry land appear.” And it was so.
Actual Greek: Καὶ εἶπεν ὁ θεός Συναχθήτω τὸ ὕδωρ τὸ ὑποκάτω τοῦ οὐρανοῦ εἰς συναγωγὴν μίαν, καὶ ὀφθήτω ἡ ξηρά. καὶ ἐγένετο οὕτως. καὶ συνήχθη τὸ ὕδωρ τὸ ὑποκάτω τοῦ οὐρανοῦ εἰς τὰς συναγωγὰς αὐτῶν, καὶ ὤφθη ἡ ξηρά.
Literal Greek: and God said Water under the sky be brought together into one gathering, and land be seen. and like this it came to be. and the water under the sky was brought together into their groups, and the land was seen.
Actual Hebrew: וַיֹּ֣אמֶר אֱלֹהִ֗ים יִקָּו֨וּ הַמַּ֜יִם מִתַּ֤חַת הַשָּׁמַ֙יִם֙ אֶל־מָק֣וֹם אֶחָ֔ד וְתֵרָאֶ֖ה הַיַּבָּשָׁ֑ה וַֽיְהִי־כֵֽן
Literal Hebrew: and God said let the waters come together from under the heavens into one place and let the dry land see and so it came to be.
Notes:
- awkward pulling the water together in Greek
- passive seen in Hebrew?

Genesis.1.10
English: God called the dry land Earth, and the waters that were gathered together he called Seas. And God saw that it was good.
Actual Greek: καὶ ἐκάλεσεν ὁ θεὸς τὴν ξηρὰν γῆν καὶ τὰ συστήματα τῶν ὑδάτων ἐκάλεσεν θαλάσσας. καὶ εἶδεν ὁ θεὸς ὅτι καλόν.
Literal Greek: and God called the land earth and the groups of water [He] called oceans. and God said that [it was] good.
Actual Hebrew: וַיִּקְרָ֨א אֱלֹהִ֤ים ׀ לַיַּבָּשָׁה֙ אֶ֔רֶץ וּלְמִקְוֵ֥ה הַמַּ֖יִם קָרָ֣א יַמִּ֑ים וַיַּ֥רְא אֱלֹהִ֖ים כִּי־טֽוֹב׃
Literal Hebrew: and God called to the dry land earth and to the gathering of the waters [He] called seas. and God saw that [it was] good.
Notes:
-

Genesis.1.11
English: And God said, “Let the earth sprout vegetation, plants yielding seed, and fruit trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each according to its kind, on the earth.” And it was so.
Actual Greek: καὶ εἶπεν ὁ θεός Βλαστησάτω ἡ γῆ βοτάνην χόρτου, σπεῖρον σπέρμα κατὰ γένος καὶ καθ᾿ ὁμοιότητα, καὶ ξύλον κάρπιμον ποιοῦν καρπόν, οὗ τὸ σπέρμα αὐτοῦ ἐν αὐτῷ κατὰ γένος ἐπὶ τῆς γῆς. καὶ ἐγένετο οὕτως.
Literal Greek: and God said Let the earth grow pastures of grass, sowing seed according to species and according to likeness, and fruit bearing trees making fruit, the seed of which [tree] [is] in it according to species on the earth. it came to be like this.
Actual Hebrew: וַיֹּ֣אמֶר אֱלֹהִ֗ים תַּֽדְשֵׁ֤א הָאָ֙רֶץ֙ דֶּ֔שֶׁא עֵ֚שֶׂב מַזְרִ֣יעַ זֶ֔רַע עֵ֣ץ פְּרִ֞י עֹ֤שֶׂה פְּרִי֙ לְמִינ֔וֹ אֲשֶׁ֥ר זַרְעוֹ־ב֖וֹ עַל־הָאָ֑רֶץ וַֽיְהִי־כֵֽן׃
Literal Hebrew: and God said let the earth sprout pasture plants yielding seed, [and] tree of fruit making fruit [according] to which kind of seed [is] in it on the earth and so it came to be.
Notes:
- pasture and plants, construct?

Genesis.1.12
English: The earth brought forth vegetation, plants yielding seed according to their own kinds, and trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each according to its kind. And God saw that it was good.
Actual Greek:καὶ ἐξήνεγκεν ἡ γῆ βοτάνην χόρτου, σπεῖρον σπέρμα κατὰ γένος καὶ καθ᾿ ὁμοιότητα, καὶ ξύλον κάρπιμον ποιοῦν καρπόν, οὗ τὸ σπέρμα αὐτοῦ ἐν αὐτῷ κατὰ γένος ἐπὶ τῆς γῆς. καὶ εἶδεν ὁ θεὸς ὅτι καλόν.
Literal Greek: and the earth brought forth pastures of grass, sowing seed according to both species and similarity, and fruit bearing trees making fruit, the seed of which [tree] [is] in it according to species on the earth. and God saw that [it was] good.
Actual Hebrew:וַתּוֹצֵ֨א הָאָ֜רֶץ דֶּ֠שֶׁא עֵ֣שֶׂב מַזְרִ֤יעַ זֶ֙רַע֙ לְמִינֵ֔הוּ וְעֵ֧ץ עֹֽשֶׂה־פְּרִ֛י אֲשֶׁ֥ר זַרְעוֹ־ב֖וֹ לְמִינֵ֑הוּ וַיַּ֥רְא אֱלֹהִ֖ים כִּי־טֽוֹב׃
Literal Hebrew: and the earth brought forth pasture plants yielding seed [according] to kind, and tree making fruit [according] to which seed [is] in it, [according] to kind [of it]. and God saw it [was] good
Notes:
- simplicity of Hebrew at the end 
